00:56:06,457 --> 00:56:09,207
Oh, right, I was thinking
of giving this to you.

758
00:56:18,967 --> 00:56:21,767
You seemed interested
to this the other day.

759
00:56:23,137 --> 00:56:24,847
Thank you so much.

760
00:56:27,857 --> 00:56:28,687
See you around.

761
00:56:35,817 --> 00:56:36,907
Ex-boyfriend?

762
00:56:38,407 --> 00:56:40,987
Ah... yeah.

763
00:56:43,247 --> 00:56:45,787
Oh... Announce School.

764
00:56:45,907 --> 00:56:47,577
Oh, but...

765
00:56:48,707 --> 00:56:52,377
it might be really hard to get in.

766
00:56:59,927 --> 00:57:00,927
We're here.

767
00:57:02,927 --> 00:57:06,847
[Dog barking]

768
00:57:11,477 --> 00:57:12,517
I'm home.

769
00:57:12,647 --> 00:57:14,407
Welcome home!

770
00:57:14,987 --> 00:57:16,697
We have a guest,
so keep it down.

771
00:57:16,817 --> 00:57:18,027
Pardon my intrusion.

772
00:57:18,157 --> 00:57:20,407
What? Big brother,
is she your girlfriend?

773
00:57:20,407 --> 00:57:23,157
- No, she's just a friend--
- Grandma! Grandma!

774
00:57:23,287 --> 00:57:25,617
- Listen to me.
- Big brother brought his girlfriend.

775
00:57:25,617 --> 00:57:27,787
- Come in.
- Yes.

776
00:57:28,747 --> 00:57:31,417
I'm home.
Miku, take this.

777
00:57:31,537 --> 00:57:33,417
- Jun...
- Here. Here.

778
00:57:34,527 --> 00:57:35,837
We have a guest.

779
00:57:35,957 --> 00:57:38,337
Pardon my intrusion.

780
00:57:38,467 --> 00:57:42,467
[Train crossing guard bell ringing]

781
00:57:43,807 --> 00:57:47,097
[Train passing by]

782
00:57:47,227 --> 00:57:48,267
Kuroda.

783
00:57:49,347 --> 00:57:51,017
What does this mean?

784
00:57:53,687 --> 00:57:57,357
Oh, this is a conjunction.

785
00:57:57,897 --> 00:57:59,777
It connects this and that...

786
00:58:00,277 --> 00:58:01,987
Oh? This one?

787
00:58:02,117 --> 00:58:03,117
Yes.

788
00:58:03,407 --> 00:58:06,577
I get it!	I understand it now.

789
00:58:08,037 --> 00:58:10,207
What about this one?

790
00:58:13,997 --> 00:58:15,087
What's the matter?

791
00:58:15,957 --> 00:58:18,547
Oh... nothing.

792
00:58:18,757 --> 00:58:20,507
I'm coming in.

793
00:58:21,047 --> 00:58:22,467
What are you doing here?

794
00:58:22,677 --> 00:58:24,507
I brought tea.

795
00:58:26,887 --> 00:58:29,807
Um, Ms. Nozomi,
would black tea be all right?

796
00:58:29,937 --> 00:58:32,397
This is all the sweets we had.

797
00:58:32,517 --> 00:58:34,937
It's okay. I love dumplings.

798
00:58:35,067 --> 00:58:36,777
That's good to know...

799
00:58:37,777 --> 00:58:42,277
Ms. Nozomi and Big Brother,
which one of you confessed first?

800
00:58:42,277 --> 00:58:44,777
Huh?! No, I...

801
00:58:45,117 --> 00:58:48,907
There's someone I like in my class.

802
00:58:49,037 --> 00:58:50,907
Oh, is that so!

803
00:58:51,327 --> 00:58:55,497
But I can't speak well.
What do you think I should do?

804
00:58:57,377 --> 00:58:59,587
Let's see...

805
00:59:00,007 --> 00:59:01,757
What's important...

806
00:59:03,467 --> 00:59:07,677
is that you don't lie about
how you really feel.

807
00:59:11,687 --> 00:59:13,727
Miku, that's enough, okay?

808
00:59:14,477 --> 00:59:16,477
- Okay.
- Good.

809
00:59:16,607 --> 00:59:17,937
Thank you.

810
00:59:18,777 --> 00:59:21,817
Ms. Nozomi and Big brother,
you guys look great!

811
00:59:21,947 --> 00:59:22,857
Huh?

812
00:59:23,107 --> 00:59:24,447
Enjoy yourselves.

813
00:59:32,867 --> 00:59:35,877
[Train crossing guard bell ringing]

814
00:59:38,587 --> 00:59:41,587
Is that okay?
I don't want to mislead her.

815
00:59:42,547 --> 00:59:43,927
Well, I don't mind.

816
00:59:46,257 --> 00:59:50,847
That reminds me, are you gonna
go to that announce school?

817
00:59:51,597 --> 00:59:53,637
It's not for me.

818
00:59:53,977 --> 00:59:56,017
Don't give up before you even try.

819
00:59:56,977 --> 01:00:00,187
I like your broadcast show.

820
01:00:07,907 --> 01:00:08,907
Come here for a second.

821
01:00:17,997 --> 01:00:18,917
Try shooting it.

822
01:00:19,127 --> 01:00:22,047
- Why?
- Just do it.

823
01:00:34,847 --> 01:00:37,187
I'm really bad at it.

824
01:00:37,307 --> 01:00:39,147
- I know.
- What?

825
01:00:39,307 --> 01:00:40,857
I saw you at basketball practice.

826
01:00:42,897 --> 01:00:44,107
Can I put it here?

827
01:00:44,437 --> 01:00:45,697
Yes.

828
01:00:56,327 --> 01:00:57,957
Use the spring in your knees

829
01:00:58,787 --> 01:01:00,587
to pull your upper body up.

830
01:01:03,797 --> 01:01:05,337
You're putting too much force.

831
01:01:06,927 --> 01:01:07,927
And...

832
01:01:12,427 --> 01:01:13,807
at about this angle...

833
01:01:16,097 --> 01:01:18,937
and.. finally,
with your wrist.

834
01:01:29,107 --> 01:01:30,117
Give me that.

835
01:01:30,237 --> 01:01:31,157
[Dribbling]

836
01:01:33,027 --> 01:01:34,827
Shape your hands like a rice ball...

837
01:01:35,787 --> 01:01:36,787
And jump.

838
01:01:41,247 --> 01:01:42,087
Your wrist.

839
01:01:42,497 --> 01:01:43,587
Like a rice ball...

840
01:01:47,337 --> 01:01:48,217
Oh, that's good.

841
01:01:49,757 --> 01:01:50,927
Oh, that was close.

842
01:01:51,547 --> 01:01:53,467
- My knee...
- Bend your knees as far as they will go.

843
01:02:03,057 --> 01:02:04,107
Kuroda.

844
01:02:04,817 --> 01:02:05,817
Hm?

845
01:02:06,737 --> 01:02:13,117
I really resisted quitting soccer.

846
01:02:14,737 --> 01:02:16,867
I got into a huge fight with my dad...

847
01:02:18,657 --> 01:02:23,287
and my grandma defended me...
with that body.

848
01:02:24,997 --> 01:02:27,127
Even Miku was considerate of me.

849
01:02:28,377 --> 01:02:31,587
So I finally gave up.

850
01:02:34,217 --> 01:02:37,427
But... sometimes I wonder.

851
01:02:38,677 --> 01:02:41,557
"Why do I have to put up with this?"

852
01:02:42,377 --> 01:02:45,877
<i>[ I don't want to quit. I
don't want to give up. ]</i>

853
01:02:52,317 --> 01:02:53,447
But that day...

854
01:02:54,657 --> 01:02:56,947
when you said to me, "I can do it again,"

855
01:02:59,367 --> 01:03:01,077
I felt so much better.

856
01:03:19,287 --> 01:03:21,366
<i>[ Thanks for today! I
understand quite a lot. Next time! ]</i>

857
01:03:21,378 --> 01:03:23,127
<i>[That's great. Feel free
to contact me anytime ]</i>

858
01:03:26,417 --> 01:03:27,397
<i>[ Matsumoto, I'll come to support you... ]</i>

859
01:03:27,397 --> 01:03:29,187
This curve

860
01:03:29,647 --> 01:03:34,777
approaches the x-axis
as close as possible,

861
01:03:34,907 --> 01:03:38,907
but never intersects it.

862
01:03:41,447 --> 01:03:43,787
<i>Are you busy lately?</i>

863
01:03:44,367 --> 01:03:47,377
<i>You haven't been writing
in the notebook like you used to.</i>

864
01:03:47,587 --> 01:03:49,297
<i>I'm a little worried.</i>

865
01:04:02,267 --> 01:04:03,847
<i>It's all right.</i>

866
01:04:05,017 --> 01:04:06,977
<i>Just a little busy...</i>

867
01:04:08,477 --> 01:04:09,567
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

868
01:04:09,817 --> 01:04:13,817
["rendez-vous" by yonawo plays]

869
01:04:14,147 --> 01:04:20,037
<i>♪ On a clear night, a
continent of clouds floats</i>

870
01:04:21,947 --> 01:04:25,827
<i>I guess everything comes to an end.</i>

871
01:04:29,377 --> 01:04:34,797
<i>For the past 3 years, we've talked in
front of the mic like this every week, </i>

872
01:04:36,177 --> 01:04:39,347
<i>and it seemed like that time
would go on forever,</i>

873
01:04:42,347 --> 01:04:47,307
<i>but this month, us third-years
will be retiring.</i>

874
01:04:51,897 --> 01:04:53,527
<i>♪ The moon shines,</i>

875
01:04:53,527 --> 01:04:57,447
<i>♪ remembering this mysterious day</i>

876
01:04:57,517 --> 01:04:59,755
<i>[ You were so kind to me and I really
enjoyed my life! Thank you so much.</i>

877
01:04:59,767 --> 01:05:00,517
<i>Kuroda ]</i>

878
01:05:18,837 --> 01:05:20,547
Oh, Erino!

879
01:05:21,547 --> 01:05:23,637
- It's Setoyama!
- What?!

880
01:05:27,847 --> 01:05:28,687
What's going on?

881
01:05:28,807 --> 01:05:31,647
Setoyama<i>-kyun</i> said,
"Let's go to Class A."

882
01:05:31,647 --> 01:05:36,027
Huh? No, I'm just wondering if I can
borrow your world history book.

883
01:05:36,147 --> 01:05:39,237
Sure, you can borrow mine.

884
01:05:46,697 --> 01:05:49,707
[Nozomi and Yuko talking]

885
01:05:53,287 --> 01:05:54,337
Here.

886
01:05:54,457 --> 01:05:55,707
- Thank you.
- Than--

887
01:05:56,767 --> 01:05:57,217
Thanks.

888
01:05:57,917 --> 01:06:00,217
That's right, we're playing
soccer at the ball game,

889
01:06:00,337 --> 01:06:01,297
and my super play--

890
01:06:01,427 --> 01:06:02,597
What are you guys talking?

891
01:06:02,717 --> 01:06:07,807
Yuko, don't interrupt
my time with Erino.

892
01:06:07,977 --> 01:06:10,727
Ugh, gross!
Get out! Get out!

893
01:06:10,847 --> 01:06:12,267
You idiot.

894
01:06:13,107 --> 01:06:16,647
Hey, hey, hey, Setoyama came to
borrow a textbook from Erino.

895
01:06:16,647 --> 01:06:18,147
All the way from Class E.

896
01:06:18,277 --> 01:06:21,205
It's frustrating, but
they look good together!

897
01:06:21,217 --> 01:06:22,197
Ah, cool!

898
01:06:22,317 --> 01:06:23,657
They're too beautiful.

899
01:06:23,777 --> 01:06:25,947
- They're perfect, right?
- They are.

900
01:06:36,917 --> 01:06:38,417
Yano...

901
01:06:43,757 --> 01:06:46,097
Can we talk for a second?

902
01:06:51,897 --> 01:06:53,807
The other day,
you were with someone...

903
01:06:54,647 --> 01:06:55,647
are you...

904
01:06:59,027 --> 01:07:00,357
going out with him?

905
01:07:02,777 --> 01:07:04,817
No, I'm not.

906
01:07:05,947 --> 01:07:09,497
We're just... friends.

907
01:07:12,037 --> 01:07:13,247
I see...

908
01:07:15,077 --> 01:07:16,627
Just friends.

909
01:07:20,087 --> 01:07:21,167
Listen,

910
01:07:23,587 --> 01:07:26,717
you think we could give
it another shot, us dating?

911
01:07:49,287 --> 01:07:50,497
[Phone beep]

912
01:07:55,477 --> 01:08:01,567
<i>[ My English score went up!
I seriously owe it to you, Kuroda!
Thank you!
See you tomorrow! ]</i>

913
01:08:03,007 --> 01:08:04,837
It has to end now.

914
01:08:19,227 --> 01:08:21,437
[Tapping on phone]

915
01:08:21,507 --> 01:08:25,007
<i>[ I have something to tell you.
Are you free tomorrow? ]</i>

916
01:08:25,007 --> 01:08:28,137
<i>[ What? Is something the matter? ]</i>

917
01:08:30,927 --> 01:08:38,117
<i>[ I have to tell you in person,
see you tomorrow. ]</i>

918
01:08:39,647 --> 01:08:41,447
<i>[ Erino Matsumoto ]</i>

919
01:08:43,377 --> 01:08:44,547
Good morning.

920
01:08:46,337 --> 01:08:47,967
- Yesterday, you said--
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!

921
01:08:48,087 --> 01:08:50,057
Who was that guy this morning?
Your boyfriend?

922
01:08:50,237 --> 01:08:50,877
Huh?

923
01:08:50,927 --> 01:08:53,517
You were talking to someone
from Nishi-High, right?

924
01:08:54,017 --> 01:08:57,377
Oh, he initiated the talk,
so we just casually chatted.

925
01:08:57,377 --> 01:08:59,647
But you were in a
really good mood.

926
01:09:00,017 --> 01:09:01,477
Yeah, that!

927
01:09:01,607 --> 01:09:03,987
He did ask me
"please go out with me."

928
01:09:04,107 --> 01:09:06,147
- What?!
- What are you gonna do?

929
01:09:06,737 --> 01:09:09,497
He's a nice guy,
and he doesn't like anyone else,

930
01:09:09,497 --> 01:09:11,077
so I don't mind going out with him.

931
01:09:12,447 --> 01:09:13,787
For real?

932
01:09:13,997 --> 01:09:18,537
There might be someone nearby

933
01:09:19,287 --> 01:09:20,837
who cares more about you.

934
01:09:21,667 --> 01:09:22,497
What?

935
01:09:24,127 --> 01:09:26,837
Huh? You mean Yoneda?

936
01:09:29,467 --> 01:09:31,427
No, it's not. I just...

937
01:09:32,637 --> 01:09:34,917
What? You know something?

938
01:09:38,557 --> 01:09:41,307
You said you'd help me, right?

939
01:09:41,687 --> 01:09:43,017
Was that a lie?

940
01:09:43,147 --> 01:09:44,107
No, it's not a lie!

941
01:09:44,227 --> 01:09:46,067
You're the worst!

942
01:09:47,487 --> 01:09:49,857
Hold on.
What are you talking about?

943
01:09:51,027 --> 01:09:52,077
Erino.

944
01:09:52,777 --> 01:09:54,947
You and Yoneda have
gotten close lately, right?

945
01:09:54,947 --> 01:09:57,037
Huh? It's nothing.
It's normal.

946
01:09:57,457 --> 01:10:01,187
What "normal"? Aren't you casual with
the boys at Nishi-High too?

947
01:10:02,077 --> 01:10:03,507
What are you saying?

948
01:10:03,507 --> 01:10:05,837
I don't like you directing
that jealousy at me.

949
01:10:05,837 --> 01:10:08,357
I don't even like Yoneda.

950
01:10:08,357 --> 01:10:09,837
How would I know that?!

951
01:10:09,837 --> 01:10:11,887
- Yuko...
- Liar, be quiet!

952
01:10:14,217 --> 01:10:17,017
Look, no matter who likes who,

953
01:10:17,017 --> 01:10:19,167
you have no business with it

954
01:10:19,167 --> 01:10:21,757
and I'm saying it's pointless
to worry about that.

955
01:10:21,807 --> 01:10:23,267
Stop taking it out on people.

956
01:10:27,437 --> 01:10:30,237
You are always right.

957
01:10:31,737 --> 01:10:32,987
You're right...

958
01:10:34,157 --> 01:10:35,077
and insensitive.

959
01:10:37,447 --> 01:10:39,077
[Chair violently pulled]

960
01:10:50,927 --> 01:10:52,717
[Door opening]

961
01:10:53,257 --> 01:10:56,257
[Yuko and Moe talking]

962
01:11:00,097 --> 01:11:02,347
- Hey!
- Hey...

963
01:11:16,697 --> 01:11:17,907
Did something happen?

964
01:11:22,917 --> 01:11:26,347
I went to the library, but you weren't
there, so I went looking for you.

965
01:11:28,337 --> 01:11:29,707
Oh, the plan...

966
01:11:30,467 --> 01:11:33,887
Wanna go to the library?
Or here would be fine.

967
01:11:36,387 --> 01:11:37,927
Yes... you're right...

968
01:11:44,807 --> 01:11:45,727
All right!

969
01:11:58,327 --> 01:11:59,907
[Setoyama sighs]

970
01:12:00,327 --> 01:12:03,787
I can't wait to practice.

971
01:12:10,757 --> 01:12:13,167
My friends got into a fight...

972
01:12:15,427 --> 01:12:17,137
Not you?

973
01:12:22,477 --> 01:12:23,807
Yeah.

974
01:12:26,597 --> 01:12:29,017
It all started with me.

975
01:12:34,447 --> 01:12:36,777
Friends getting jealous,

976
01:12:39,077 --> 01:12:41,237
not being able to tell the truth...

977
01:12:42,617 --> 01:12:45,287
and in the end because I'm indecisive...

978
01:12:47,247 --> 01:12:50,247
What if you just tell them honestly?

979
01:12:55,257 --> 01:12:57,757
When I think I have to say something,

980
01:12:58,427 --> 01:13:01,137
I get so flustered that
I can't say anything at all.

981
01:13:04,927 --> 01:13:07,807
Then... just let it out.

982
01:13:09,807 --> 01:13:10,857
What?

983
01:13:11,607 --> 01:13:13,477
I don't know what's going on,

984
01:13:13,607 --> 01:13:16,527
but for now, your voice is too low.

985
01:13:18,277 --> 01:13:19,157
Yes.

986
01:13:21,327 --> 01:13:24,177
Facing that mountain over there,
yell out whatever you want.

987
01:13:25,147 --> 01:13:25,957
I can't.

988
01:13:26,657 --> 01:13:27,667
Huh?

989
01:13:29,207 --> 01:13:30,377
Ah!

990
01:13:30,377 --> 01:13:32,167
[Voice echoing]

991
01:13:33,167 --> 01:13:35,417
Oh... go on!

992
01:13:41,427 --> 01:13:42,307
Oh...

993
01:13:44,717 --> 01:13:46,807
Are you even trying?

994
01:13:47,657 --> 01:13:50,147
Okay, one more time.

995
01:13:55,937 --> 01:13:57,567
Oh!

996
01:13:59,237 --> 01:14:01,157
Ah!

997
01:14:04,117 --> 01:14:06,077
Oh!

998
01:14:16,957 --> 01:14:18,507
All right!

999
01:14:27,637 --> 01:14:30,687
They had a fight because
of your ex-boyfriend?

1000
01:14:31,397 --> 01:14:33,687
No, that's not it.

1001
01:14:35,267 --> 01:14:38,187
Do you still like him?

1002
01:14:44,027 --> 01:14:48,997
Yano confessed his feelings for me
and we started going out,

1003
01:14:49,827 --> 01:14:55,667
but even then...
I couldn't tell him how I felt.

1004
01:14:57,247 --> 01:14:58,417
And then he said...

1005
01:15:00,297 --> 01:15:05,297
"I have no idea what you're thinking,"
so he dumped me.

1006
01:15:09,137 --> 01:15:14,187
For now, why don't you
say it out clearly next time?

1007
01:15:16,017 --> 01:15:17,067
Next time?

1008
01:15:17,317 --> 01:15:20,647
Next time...
you find someone you like.

1009
01:15:31,997 --> 01:15:33,537
Setoyama...

1010
01:15:35,327 --> 01:15:37,037
what do you about Erino?

1011
01:15:38,547 --> 01:15:39,547
What?

1012
01:15:41,757 --> 01:15:43,967
It seems you two have gotten closer...

1013
01:15:49,427 --> 01:15:50,727
You and Erino...

1014
01:15:52,517 --> 01:15:54,457
I hope things work out for you two.

1015
01:16:17,497 --> 01:16:20,957
Oh, no, I... didn't mean to...

1016
01:16:24,547 --> 01:16:25,627
"Didn't mean to"?

1017
01:16:26,387 --> 01:16:29,137
No, it's not that. It's just...

1018
01:16:30,137 --> 01:16:31,267
Kuroda.

1019
01:16:36,267 --> 01:16:37,607
